# 13. Use the Reverse DNS to find out the name of the server linked to the 10.51.1.81 IP address

dig +short -x 10.51.1.81

#nslookup 10.51.1.81 also works - just read the domain name section
#man dig (somain information groper) - tool for interrogating DNS name servers
#+short: prints the terse answer; otherwise verbose form printed
#-x: option so you can provide the address
#-q: allows you to provide the name to get address as result instead
